[The weather has a limiting factor on the insects, especially the
biting midges _Culicoides_ that carry the disease. As the weather
becomes colder they should die out, and the cycle of the disease
seems to die out as well. It is getting pretty cool up in the
Northeastern US, but without a hard killing frost these insects will
continue to spread their disease.

Since it is hunting season, there are more people out to observe the
movement of the cervids, and consequently, more affected animals may
be seen than if the deaths had occurred in June. - Mod.TG]

